WEBVTT

00:06.041 --> 00:09.875
A NETFLIX SERIES

00:26.666 --> 00:30.208
Could we roll up the window?
I can't feel my toes anymore.

00:30.291 --> 00:32.958
Roll up one side,
the other rolls down. Look.

00:36.916 --> 00:38.791
All right. I'm cold!

00:43.916 --> 00:45.500
How did you get that guy

00:45.583 --> 00:47.791
to give you Marcus' parents' address?

00:47.875 --> 00:50.083
I said we had switched the presents again.

00:50.666 --> 00:52.333
-Hold on. He believed you?
-No need.

00:52.916 --> 00:56.708
I offered to go out for a drink.
He stopped listening altogether.

00:57.500 --> 00:59.500
-What an idiot.
-Good job!

01:14.791 --> 01:17.041
What do you think about Marcus' track?

01:17.125 --> 01:18.875
VERNO UR THE BEST
VERNO'S PISSED

01:18.958 --> 01:21.083
I don't have time for this bullshit.

01:21.166 --> 01:23.666
The one where he says
women should shut it?

01:23.750 --> 01:26.708
-Yeah, that one.
-Tell you what, Marcus.

01:26.791 --> 01:28.500
You should shut it.

01:28.583 --> 01:31.666
Shut it. If you have something to say,
say it to my face.

01:31.750 --> 01:33.333
Stop hiding around Paris.

01:33.416 --> 01:35.500
Spit it out. Why do you hate him?

01:35.583 --> 01:37.458
You know what? Stop filming.

02:00.375 --> 02:01.208
<i>Hello?</i>

02:01.291 --> 02:02.500
I saw Verno's video.

02:02.583 --> 02:06.125
-I haven't. What does it say?
<i>-He's not in a Christmas mood.</i>

02:06.208 --> 02:07.333
What's his deal?

02:07.416 --> 02:09.458
<i>I don't want to play his game.</i>

02:09.541 --> 02:14.083
-Anyway. Have you heard from Mel?
<i>-She's still mad. She's not coming.</i>

02:14.166 --> 02:15.625
Have to do without her.

02:15.708 --> 02:17.500
My mom's going to be bummed.

02:17.583 --> 02:20.500
Come on, man.
She's happy to have you, bro.

02:20.583 --> 02:22.291
<i>-Her son.</i>
-You're not wrong.

02:22.375 --> 02:26.000
Given the situation with the old man,
it may be best not to introduce Mel now.

02:26.083 --> 02:29.416
-Isn't she the perfect daughter-in-law?
-I'm not the perfect son.

02:29.958 --> 02:30.791
Talk later.

02:40.875 --> 02:44.333
CHRISTMAS MAGIC

02:45.250 --> 02:47.166
Marcus, my son!

02:48.125 --> 02:49.750
Come in quick. It's cold.

02:49.833 --> 02:52.291
-I have the prettiest mom.
-Sure, right.

02:53.791 --> 02:56.375
Two Christmases without you.
How could you?

02:56.458 --> 02:58.625
-It's work, Mom.
-Work, sure.

02:58.708 --> 02:59.541
Here.

03:00.458 --> 03:02.500
You have something to make up for.

03:02.583 --> 03:04.708
Everyone's been dying to see you.

03:05.375 --> 03:07.041
-Everyone?
-Everyone.

03:07.125 --> 03:08.541
Today is Christmas.

03:08.625 --> 03:11.458
-No negative topics. You hear me?
-Yeah.

03:12.458 --> 03:14.166
I'll put these in some water.

03:25.250 --> 03:26.833
-Hi, everyone.
-Marcus!

03:28.125 --> 03:30.291
You found time to come see us?

03:34.500 --> 03:36.875
Glad to see the atmosphere is a delight.

03:37.875 --> 03:40.375
You lost your trial.
Not your sense of humor.

03:40.458 --> 03:42.125
-Jean-Louis.
-It's okay, Mom.

03:43.291 --> 03:44.458
Glad to see you, Dad.

03:45.333 --> 03:46.416
Hey, bro.

03:47.125 --> 03:48.833
You're less handsome than I recall.

03:48.916 --> 03:51.083
-Time hasn't been kind.
-Don't listen to him.

03:51.166 --> 03:53.375
You're more handsome than ever.

03:58.625 --> 04:00.833
-All right. Let's get to work.
-Yeah.

04:04.541 --> 04:05.625
What are all these?

04:05.708 --> 04:09.250
For all the Christmases I missed.
Mel's presents too.

04:09.333 --> 04:11.625
-Can we open the presents?
-We're waiting for Mel.

04:13.000 --> 04:14.541
He wanted to buy The Simones?

04:15.125 --> 04:16.458
-The bastard.
-Never.

04:16.541 --> 04:18.750
-Come on, champ!
-Go!

04:19.416 --> 04:22.666
Think you can use us like that?
It's an insult to women.

04:23.416 --> 04:24.791
Even your mother.

04:24.875 --> 04:26.375
I'll mention his mother.

04:29.375 --> 04:30.500
Is she on her way?

04:30.583 --> 04:32.000
No, Mom. Mel isn't…

04:33.291 --> 04:35.500
That must be her.

04:35.583 --> 04:37.333
-I'll get it.
-It's not her.

04:38.208 --> 04:41.500
I can't wait. So great to have her here.

04:41.583 --> 04:43.625
-Here she is!
-Who?

04:43.708 --> 04:45.000
Your fiancée, Mel.

04:47.625 --> 04:48.458
No…

04:57.625 --> 05:00.125
Hello! Well, I…

05:00.208 --> 05:01.958
I'm delighted to meet you.

05:03.333 --> 05:05.333
-Hello, miss.
-Hello, young man.

05:05.416 --> 05:07.875
You must be the big brother. Right?

05:09.000 --> 05:11.166
-My husband, Jean-Louis.
-Jean-Louis.

05:11.250 --> 05:12.958
My eldest, Jean-Luc.

05:13.041 --> 05:15.500
-Nice to meet you.
-His wife, Chance.

05:15.583 --> 05:17.916
-Chance…
-And my youngest.

05:18.000 --> 05:19.791
-Marie-Jeanne.
-MJ!

05:22.000 --> 05:22.958
MJ.

05:23.041 --> 05:24.625
And you know Jean-Marc.

05:25.958 --> 05:27.541
I think we're done here.

05:27.625 --> 05:29.708
-We're good.
-Jean-Marc, then.

05:29.791 --> 05:31.875
I'll show you the bathroom.
Want to freshen up?

05:31.958 --> 05:33.333
Sure, babe.

05:33.416 --> 05:35.416
-Yes.
-What's wrong with you?

05:36.958 --> 05:39.250
Cool it, Jean-Marc!

05:39.958 --> 05:42.666
Very funny.
A tradition on my father's side.

05:43.958 --> 05:45.291
Jean-Marc sounds good.

05:45.958 --> 05:49.375
-I think it's better than Marcus.
-Why are you here?

05:49.458 --> 05:52.375
Gate-crashing your family Christmas,
talking nonsense?

05:52.958 --> 05:55.291
-Sound familiar?
-I didn't pretend to be your man.

05:55.375 --> 05:57.666
You did try to become him though.

05:58.250 --> 06:01.458
-What game are you playing?
-I can ask you the same.

06:01.541 --> 06:03.416
Why didn't you say I'm not Mel?

06:03.500 --> 06:07.541
You don't know them!
They wouldn't get it. I don't either.

06:09.500 --> 06:11.125
-When is Mel coming over?
-Never.

06:12.375 --> 06:13.458
It's complicated.

06:16.083 --> 06:18.166
What am I going to tell them?

06:21.708 --> 06:23.000
Fuck…

06:27.041 --> 06:29.833
-Yeah?
-What are you doing?

06:29.916 --> 06:32.541
We're freezing. Did you talk to Marcus?

06:32.625 --> 06:34.041
Even better!

06:36.833 --> 06:37.666
Just a sec.

06:37.750 --> 06:40.125
It's the whole blow-drying thing.

06:41.625 --> 06:44.333
Women… What are you doing?

06:44.416 --> 06:45.708
His family thinks I'm Mel.

06:45.791 --> 06:47.875
You don't even look like her.

06:48.458 --> 06:51.500
I know. It's insane. It's totally weird.

06:51.583 --> 06:56.541
He's embarrassed. You should see his face.
I'll drag it out to piss him off.

06:57.125 --> 06:58.458
Open up. What are you doing?

06:58.541 --> 07:01.291
-Hold on. We've got to cash in on this.
-Yes.

07:01.375 --> 07:03.375
-Infiltration mission.
-What?

07:03.458 --> 07:04.916
<i>Stay in character.</i>

07:05.000 --> 07:06.833
<i>Look around his room.</i>

07:06.916 --> 07:09.208
<i>Go through his stuff. Look for clues.</i>

07:09.291 --> 07:13.083
That's where we should be looking.
His parents will give you a lead.

07:13.166 --> 07:17.000
I don't know. His family doesn't have
anything to do with it.

07:17.083 --> 07:21.458
We're not trying to expose them.
Don't forget what he tried to do to us.

07:21.541 --> 07:23.416
He wanted to play. Let's play.

07:28.208 --> 07:29.166
I'll call you back.

07:33.291 --> 07:34.125
Mel.

07:36.500 --> 07:37.416
LIFE IS BETTER WITH ME

07:37.500 --> 07:39.333
ONLY THE SUN CAN WARM ME UP

07:40.416 --> 07:41.791
I don't look like her.

08:03.708 --> 08:04.583
Yeah, okay.

08:06.916 --> 08:07.750
Shit.

08:22.291 --> 08:23.208
Hi, Mel.

08:23.958 --> 08:25.208
Thank God, finally.

08:25.291 --> 08:26.333
I have an idea.

08:27.000 --> 08:29.958
Pretend to be Mel for ten minutes or so.

08:30.500 --> 08:33.375
Act as if you received a text. Then leave.

08:35.666 --> 08:38.333
-Did you change something?
-Don't worry, babe.

08:38.958 --> 08:40.375
Everything will be fine.

08:49.958 --> 08:53.166
-Is something wrong?
-No.

08:53.250 --> 08:55.500
Tell us how you met.

08:55.583 --> 08:58.500
-We want to know everything.
-Yes, everything.

08:58.583 --> 09:00.750
-For one of my videos.
-At one of my concerts.

09:02.541 --> 09:05.791
First times are like that.
Everyone remembers it differently.

09:05.875 --> 09:07.291
Yes. Actually,

09:07.375 --> 09:09.166
Marcus is a fan of mine.

09:09.250 --> 09:11.416
He contacted me for a collab.

09:11.500 --> 09:12.666
A collab?

09:12.750 --> 09:15.166
-It's--
-She's a fan of mine, actually.

09:15.250 --> 09:17.416
-Initially.
-I don't remember that.

09:17.500 --> 09:19.250
She knows all of my songs.

09:19.333 --> 09:20.791
-Not true.
-Yes.

09:20.875 --> 09:22.333
-I'm not a fan.
-You are.

09:23.916 --> 09:26.125
The food is ready. It's time to eat.

09:27.208 --> 09:28.958
No! Let's open the presents.

09:29.041 --> 09:31.375
-Not now. We're hungry.
-Yes, we are.

09:31.458 --> 09:33.208
Yes, I'm hungry too.

09:33.291 --> 09:35.666
Come on. Get up.

09:35.750 --> 09:36.708
That's nice.

09:36.791 --> 09:40.291
Stop! You're under the mistletoe.

09:40.875 --> 09:42.208
You have to kiss.

09:45.625 --> 09:47.541
-No. It's okay.
-There's no need.

09:47.625 --> 09:49.458
-Dad's here and all.
-Come on.

09:49.541 --> 09:51.000
-Come on, bro.
-Come on.

09:51.083 --> 09:53.416
You kissed every girl
in the family as a kid.

09:53.500 --> 09:54.708
That's true.

09:56.291 --> 09:57.333
Awkward.

09:57.416 --> 10:00.250
<i>-</i>That's true, but Mel is shy.
-Yes.

10:00.333 --> 10:02.875
With all those followers of yours?
I don't believe it.

10:02.958 --> 10:06.833
-Do me a favor. My camera is waiting.
-Come on.

10:06.916 --> 10:09.541
-There's no way out.
-Come on. One kiss.

10:11.458 --> 10:13.708
I didn't have time to take a picture.

10:13.791 --> 10:15.916
Kiss for real so we can eat.

10:16.000 --> 10:17.291
Yes, do a real kiss.

10:17.375 --> 10:18.541
So we can eat.

10:20.208 --> 10:22.166
-Come on.
-Come on, bro.

10:33.500 --> 10:36.416
I've got it on camera.
I'll send it to my cousins.

10:36.500 --> 10:39.250
They don't believe me
when I say you have a fiancée.

10:39.333 --> 10:41.375
I have proof.

10:42.750 --> 10:45.041
Don't stay stuck together until next year.

10:53.791 --> 10:55.125
-Our turn.
-A kiss.

10:58.583 --> 10:59.875
Mom? Are you ready?

10:59.958 --> 11:01.166
I'm ready. Go ahead.

11:02.708 --> 11:04.541
-Did you get it?
-One more time.

11:06.291 --> 11:07.458
How about now?

11:07.541 --> 11:09.541
That one's a keeper. I'll take it.

11:12.666 --> 11:14.458
They make vegan foie gras now.

11:15.958 --> 11:18.250
-They call it faux gras.
-No.

11:18.833 --> 11:19.833
Yeah, it's not bad.

11:20.750 --> 11:23.916
Victoire buys it.
She's been into vegetarianism lately.

11:29.166 --> 11:32.333
I have to go.
Victoire and her parents are about to eat.

11:32.416 --> 11:35.333
We can't hang around here,
freezing our asses off.

11:36.583 --> 11:37.500
Okay. Let's go.

11:38.625 --> 11:39.916
Let's go. Transfer.

11:40.750 --> 11:42.458
-Drop me off?
-At your place?

11:42.541 --> 11:43.791
No, I have plans.

11:45.500 --> 11:49.333
-You're more flexible.
-You noticed. Pilates will do that.

11:50.250 --> 11:53.333
Lila can handle it.
She'll dig up some serious dirt.

11:54.625 --> 11:56.250
-Delicious.
-It's Christmas.

11:56.333 --> 11:58.208
-We're in for a treat.
-Can I help?

11:59.000 --> 12:00.750
Thanks, Mel. You're sweet.

12:00.833 --> 12:04.000
-But you're our guest. Let us handle it.
-Okay.

12:04.083 --> 12:06.250
Can I help serve, then?

12:06.333 --> 12:07.791
Weren't we right to invite you?

12:08.416 --> 12:11.875
We've been dying to meet
this famous Mel. Right, Gloria?

12:12.458 --> 12:13.458
Eagerly waiting.

12:14.583 --> 12:16.000
Me too. I…

12:16.541 --> 12:18.833
I couldn't wait to meet you.

12:23.875 --> 12:25.125
Anyway, it's…

12:25.208 --> 12:27.291
it's wonderful for Marcus,

12:27.375 --> 12:29.875
Jean-Marc, to spend Christmas with family.

12:31.208 --> 12:33.416
With the trial and everything,

12:34.000 --> 12:36.250
he's been kind of down lately.

12:40.500 --> 12:43.625
Good thing there haven't been
any further revelations.

12:44.375 --> 12:46.375
I mean, at the same time.

12:48.666 --> 12:52.416
-Like old stories, for instance…
-Poor thing. It's hard for him.

12:54.416 --> 12:57.875
It's hard for everyone.
But today is Christmas.

12:59.708 --> 13:00.791
No negative topics.

13:00.875 --> 13:03.125
Positive vibes only.

13:03.208 --> 13:05.166
Positive vibes. Yes.

13:05.250 --> 13:07.166
-Would you give me a hand?
-Yes.

13:07.250 --> 13:11.041
-It looks delicious. What is it?
-Chicken mafe. His favorite.

13:11.125 --> 13:12.541
-Of course.
-Shall we?

13:12.625 --> 13:13.833
Let's go, ladies.

13:14.458 --> 13:15.958
-After you.
-Food's ready!

13:34.125 --> 13:35.583
It's delicious, really.

13:35.666 --> 13:37.583
Thank you, Mel.

13:37.666 --> 13:42.166
The sauce with the manioc leaves.
It's called saka-saka. And we sing…

13:48.041 --> 13:50.541
-You remember?
-Of course. Are you crazy?

13:50.625 --> 13:51.916
Anyway, Mom…

13:52.583 --> 13:55.291
-This here is out of this world.
-That's right.

13:55.375 --> 13:56.958
How's your music going?

13:57.958 --> 13:59.500
Yeah, it's fine. Good.

13:59.583 --> 14:00.500
Tell us more.

14:00.583 --> 14:03.541
Nothing special.
I'm wrapping up some tracks.

14:03.625 --> 14:07.458
Do you plan on getting sued
for your next album? Or is once enough?

14:07.541 --> 14:08.458
Jean-Louis?

14:09.083 --> 14:10.166
You promised.

14:10.250 --> 14:12.041
What? I'm interested.

14:12.125 --> 14:14.666
-I'll show you interested.
-Let him be, Mom.

14:16.291 --> 14:18.666
No big deal.
Dad's right. I have to settle that.

14:20.666 --> 14:22.916
We filed an appeal.
The lawyer says it's cool.

14:23.416 --> 14:24.250
So it's cool.

14:25.416 --> 14:26.541
Yes, it's cool.

14:28.125 --> 14:30.791
We worked hard
so that our children could make it.

14:31.458 --> 14:32.583
Get a degree.

14:33.458 --> 14:35.666
So they could lead fine lives.

14:36.250 --> 14:37.083
But

14:37.625 --> 14:38.458
it's cool.

14:39.833 --> 14:43.291
-Thank goodness we have Jean-Luc.
-Dad, please.

14:44.208 --> 14:45.750
-Let's eat in peace.
-What?

14:47.000 --> 14:49.625
Can't I be proud you've become a dentist?

14:49.708 --> 14:51.333
Yes, but we're eating.

14:51.916 --> 14:55.583
I guess my diamond records
are nothing compared to Mr. Dentist.

14:58.666 --> 15:03.666
The reward of a lifetime…
is earned by the sweat of your brow.

15:04.750 --> 15:07.750
What defines us
are the values we embody and uphold.

15:07.833 --> 15:11.333
Our role in society
cannot be measured in diamond records.

15:11.416 --> 15:13.750
And even less in court convictions.

15:16.208 --> 15:19.125
-You're laying it on thick.
-I beg your pardon?

15:20.458 --> 15:22.666
Writing and composing your own songs,

15:22.750 --> 15:27.000
making millions of people dance,
dream, that counts for something.

15:27.083 --> 15:30.666
As Nietzsche said,
"Without music, life would be a mistake."

15:31.250 --> 15:33.333
I doubt he was talking about music videos

15:33.416 --> 15:36.125
packed with girls
squirming around half-naked.

15:36.208 --> 15:39.166
I agree. Talk about
the representation of women.

15:39.250 --> 15:41.166
I have to say it's a bit…

15:42.041 --> 15:44.375
-Degrading.
-To say the least.

15:45.083 --> 15:46.541
Don't get me started on the lyrics.

15:47.500 --> 15:49.125
Those lyrics are something.

15:49.208 --> 15:50.833
Is this my second trial?

15:50.916 --> 15:52.875
-I mean, Mel is right.
-All right.

15:53.916 --> 15:57.333
Are we done? Can we eat in peace?

15:58.833 --> 16:01.375
His videos aren't
the only ones where women…

16:01.458 --> 16:03.791
Just look around. They're all doing it.

16:03.875 --> 16:06.291
-It's systematic.
-I'd say it's systemic.

16:06.375 --> 16:10.083
Consider the message
it sends out to young people. Right, MJ?

16:10.791 --> 16:11.875
It's beyond that.

16:11.958 --> 16:16.833
This is about women's place in society,
in family. What's it like in yours?

16:16.916 --> 16:19.375
The men didn't set a foot
in the kitchen today.

16:19.458 --> 16:21.708
-There you go.
-More like in the last 30 years.

16:22.750 --> 16:24.333
Whatever, Mom. Come on.

16:25.291 --> 16:26.625
It's the truth.

16:26.708 --> 16:28.583
Never seen you or your brother.

16:28.666 --> 16:30.750
When we bring it up, they run away.

16:30.833 --> 16:33.791
-When did you ever lend a hand?
-I have to work!

16:33.875 --> 16:36.000
You have to work! Doesn't she work too?

16:36.083 --> 16:37.875
You do everything too fast.

16:38.500 --> 16:40.208
Thanks, Dad. That's it.

16:43.166 --> 16:44.083
<i>-Hello?</i>
-Yeah.

16:44.166 --> 16:47.041
-You holding up?
<i>-I'm fed up with Christmas.</i>

16:47.125 --> 16:49.250
I draw a line at Christmas Eve.

16:49.333 --> 16:53.125
It's like running two marathons
back to back. I'm not fit for it.

16:53.208 --> 16:54.458
<i>It's worse, Zack.</i>

16:54.541 --> 16:56.291
-Mel turned up.
<i>-Seriously?</i>

16:56.916 --> 16:59.416
<i>-Isn't that great news?</i>
-Not the right Mel.

17:00.583 --> 17:01.666
What do you mean?

17:01.750 --> 17:03.916
She's turning my Mom
into Simone de Beauvoir.

17:05.125 --> 17:06.375
<i>Hey, listen.</i>

17:06.458 --> 17:10.375
I can't have the real Mel here.
Or it'll be war. You get me?

17:12.375 --> 17:16.291
No, I didn't get that.
It doesn't look like she wants to come.

17:16.375 --> 17:19.750
I'll stay on my guard.
This is the Christmas of surprises.

17:19.833 --> 17:21.291
<i>-I'm on it.</i>
-I got to go.

17:21.958 --> 17:23.583
Hey there, sunshines!

17:24.375 --> 17:26.791
Today, we're doing Christmas meditations.

17:27.500 --> 17:30.166
To finish off the year
with positive emotions.

17:30.250 --> 17:33.166
Then we can turn off social media
until next year.

17:34.208 --> 17:35.541
Let's go.

17:35.625 --> 17:37.458
AWESOME!
SHE'S PERFECT

17:37.541 --> 17:38.708
ZACK CELLPHONE

17:38.791 --> 17:40.416
What a pain.

17:40.500 --> 17:41.875
What a fucking pain.

17:43.583 --> 17:45.041
I'm still here. Sorry.

17:45.791 --> 17:49.291
Let's get back to it.
Let's take a deep breath…

17:51.875 --> 17:54.541
Let's reach for our little wisdom box.

17:54.625 --> 17:56.125
You all know it by now.

17:56.208 --> 17:59.375
We're going to lock up our negative vibes.

18:00.125 --> 18:03.500
As well as the assholes we trusted
but shouldn't have.

18:04.666 --> 18:07.208
And we throw it away.

